doc.after: Germanium dioxide is also used in catalysts for polymerization in the production of polyethylene terephthalate (PET).[68] The high brilliance of the produced polyester is especially used for PET bottles marketed in Japan.[68] However, in the United States, no germanium is used for polymerization catalysts.[24] Due to the similarity between silica (SiO2) and germanium dioxide (GeO2), the silica stationary phase in some gas chromatography columns can be replaced by GeO2.[69]
